d. The emphasis throughout these selections is on metaphysical, epistemological, and religious issues: the existence and nature of God, his relation to the world, the nature of the human mind and its relation to the body, and the theory of demonstration, axioms, and definitions. For each of these topics, the editor supplements the rigorous discussions in the Ethics with informal treatments from Spinoza's other works.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEthicsvEarly works to 1800. 0aPhilosophyvEarly works to 1800. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh  aaction/act/active.  aadequate idea.  aaffect.  aambition.  aappetite.  aattribute.  ablessedness/blessed.  abody.  abody/corporeal substance/corporeal.  acause.  acertainty/certain.  aclear and distinct.  acontingency.  acontingent.  acreation/create/creator.  adefinition.  adesire.  aessence.  afreedom.  agood.  ahuman.  aidea.  aintellect/intellectual.  aknowledge.  amind.  aorder.  aperfection/perfect.  apower.  areason/reasoning.1 aCurley, Edwin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691209289zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691209289423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691209289.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK